review_comments.body:
@chcosta take a look at _PackageArchiveReader_ and _NuspecReader_ from _NuGet.Packaging_

NuGet does some parsing on filenames also, but it is imperfect and should only be used to rule out obvious non-matches. For example packageA.1.2.3 could be either: packageA.1 version: 2.3 or packageA version: 1.2.3. The only way to know for sure is to read the nuspec.

You can see the NuGet code for this here: https://github.com/NuGet/NuGet.Client/blob/dev/src/NuGet.Core/NuGet.Protocol.Core.v3/Utility/LocalFolderUtility.cs#L264

